Rip off on açaí bowls, none of the options are açaí only for the simple reason that açaí pulp is much more expensive than spinach and almond butter - result is that you’re paying açaí prices for smoothies with peanut butter. Don’t be fooled by their “hip” look, this is a scam.

Healthy, gluten free, dairy free, responsibly sourced, organic, vegan juice blends, smoothies, juice shots and bowls plus healthy snacks, brownies and cookies. Sweetener of stevia or agave is added upon request. Take out service only. Pleasant, helpful staff. Service, even when packed is quick, polite and friendly. I love their "Mucho Mango" smoothie and the chocolate chip protein cookie. Even my husband, whom is not very big on healthy eating loves the chocolate chip protein cookie!! Looking for a refreshing, healthy alternative to traditional beverage choices? I would recommend this place.

As someone who enjoys smoothies and açai bowls, it's kind of hard to dislike places like Juice Generation. I find that their menu items are ok, and it takes some modifying to get the right consistency for their smoothies. Wish they had more seasonable toppings for their bowls - I feel like the bananas are always too premature to eat and have had other fresh fruit items that weren't ready. Overall, you will get healthy items here where at the very least you'll know every ingredient going in.

Super clean atmosphere. Modern look inside. Friendly staff. My favorite thing to get here is a peanut butter split smoothie which has flaxseed oil in it. I also add some Kale to it for some extra nutrition. It's very tasty for those peanut butter lovers out there. Be sure to let the chef know that you will take any "extras" so that any smoothie portion that doesn't fit in the purchased cup will be given to you in an extra cup so nothing goes to waste and you will be satiated! Wheel chair accessible, has a clean bathroom. Not many places to sit.. more of a get and go type of place.. some communal seating outside.

Love the space but feels a bit off. They could have utilized all that space better. It's cold and all the chairs and tables are outside and nothing but space inside. Anyway, this is what l'm happy about: I ordered a Ginger Fix. The drink is never creamy enough for me so not too long ago (at a JG bway n 86th st.) "My new Fix was born!!!" I asked her to use the frozen coconut to make it creamier. So she said she would steam it and put it in. It's great! So when I came to this JG I asked them to do the same. And the gentleman who fixed my drink made it even creamier. It's like I'm in heaven now!! (Still wondering if I'll get paid when people start asking for it.) Yeah, don't think I'll hold my breath on that one. Companies always steal our ideas. However, for those of you that will try my new CREAMY Ginger Fix, ENJOY!  I have to add this cuz Elvis was so great! The guy who made my ginger fix with coconut cream wasn't there so they said they would try. A female employee made my drink and it taste like ginger water. She didn't even acknowledge me. Why is she in this business if she's not going to talk to people? Anyway, Elvis stepped up and said he would make it over for me. He heated the coconut cream like the other guy did and it came out great! I was going to leave angry but Elvis saved the day. Now I'll make a special trip just to get my drink from Elvis. That little black girl (unfortunately) needs to find another job. THANK YOU ELVIS! You're the best!!
